\f0\fs24 \cf2 <$Scr_Cs::2>
\f1\b\fs32 volt
\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 <!$Scr_Cs::2>
\f2\fs32  (unit symbol: V) is the unit of electromotive force in the International System of Units.  An electric potential difference of one volt between two points will impart one joule of energy per coulomb of charge moving between them.  Another, more practical, definition of a volt is the potential difference required to drive one amp of current through one ohm of resistance. \
